# Subagent prompt template â€” compute-infra DAG executor
# =============================================================================
# This is the per-unit prompt that gets sent to each `forge` subagent.
# One prompt per DAG unit. Subagent receives: unit spec, repo context, gates,
# and must emit: branch URL, diffstat, grade.sh output delta, completion report.
#
# Usage (when user approves execution):
#   python launch_phase.py --phase 1 --pool infra-pool --concurrency 4
# =============================================================================

prompt_template = """
You are executing DAG unit {unit_id} for the Phenotype compute/infra epic.

## Unit spec
- ID:           {unit_id}
- Title:        {title}
- Type:         {type}
- Repo:         {repo} (GitHub: KooshaPari/{repo})
- Epic:         {epic_id} â€” {epic_title}

## Standards authority
- Spine:        phenotype-registry (SOTA.md, DOMAIN_ROLES.md, LANGUAGE_PLACEMENT.md)
- Grader:       bash phenotype-registry/grade.sh --json
- Workflow:     agileplus 9-phase pipeline (Specifyâ†’Planâ†’Designâ†’Decomposeâ†’Dispatchâ†’Reviewâ†’Verifyâ†’Mergeâ†’Audit)

## Gates (must pass before claiming done)
- Tier-0: build / test-unit / fmt (or clippy/rustfmt) / lint / typecheck green
- Tier-1: cargo audit (or npm audit) / trufflehog / SBOM / LICENSE / CHANGELOG
- Tier-2: coverage â‰Ą 71% (lib) / 70% (framework) / 60% (service) per ADR-040
- Cross-repo: update phenotype-registry/projects/<repo>.json if architecture changed

## Workflow
1. **Specify** â€” read existing PR/branch relevant to this unit (look at the
   open PR list and branch list in the audit report). State in 3 lines what
   you're doing and why.
2. **Plan** â€” write the work as an agileplus-compatible work unit:
   `agileplus-specs/<NNN>-<slug>/spec.md`, `tasks/WP01.md`, `tasks/WP02.md`...
   Use `agileplus-specs/005-compute-infra-hardening/` if it doesn't exist.
3. **Design** â€” if architectural, write an ADR (PhenoSpecs `adrs/` or repo-local
   `docs/adr/`). Reference DOMAIN_ROLES for owner.
4. **Decompose** â€” break into atomic sub-tasks, each with its own acceptance test.
5. **Dispatch** â€” make the change on a new branch:
   `git checkout -b <type>/<unit-id>-<slug>`
   Commit in semantic units. Push.
6. **Review** â€” open PR with the agileplus PR template. Tag `area:compute-infra`.
7. **Verify** â€” run grade.sh on the repo. Capture JSON output. Diff vs main.
8. **Merge** â€” if all gates green AND review approval, merge with squash.
9. **Audit** â€” append audit entry to phenotype-registry/audits/<date>.json.

## Constraints
- DO NOT touch `phenotype-sdk` branch state â€” it has a mid-flight absorb operation.
- DO NOT rewrite history of shared branches.
- DO NOT commit secrets, tokens, auth.json.
- USE UTF-8 ASCII only in markdown (no smart quotes, em-dashes; see agileplus CLAUDE.md rule 2).
- FOLLOW DOMAIN_ROLES for owner assignment. If your work crosses role boundaries,
  file the unit under the OWNER's repo, not the consumer's.
- IF you discover a bug in phenotype-registry / agileplus / pheno-cli / grade.sh,
  fix it inline (dogfood â†’ fix â†’ extend), then continue.

## Deliverables (emit before claiming done)
- [ ] Branch name
- [ ] PR URL (or note "local-only" if not pushable)
- [ ] grade.sh JSON output (paste full)
- [ ] Coverage delta vs main (paste)
- [ ] Files changed (diffstat)
- [ ] Any dogfood fixes applied (list)
- [ ] Any new DAG units suggested (auto-add candidates)

## Auditor loop participation
After your unit is merged, the validator subagent will:
- Re-run grade.sh on the repo
- Diff vs your output
- Auto-add units for any regressed pillars

If you find an issue that the DAG should add a unit for, append it as:
```yaml
- {{ id: <next_id>, repo: <repo>, type: <type>, title: "...", source: auditor-loop }}
```
to a `auto_added.yaml` file in phenotype-registry/audits/.

## Reference
- Full DAG:        _compute_infra_audit/dags/compute_infra_dag.yaml
- Validator:       _compute_infra_audit/verify_deliverables.py
- Audit report:    _compute_infra_audit/report.txt
- Standards:       phenotype-registry/{DOMAIN_ROLES,LANGUAGE_PLACEMENT,SOTA,ECOSYSTEM_MAP}.md
- Workflow:        agileplus/{README,CLAUDE.md,agileplus-specs/00X-*}

Begin now. Report back with: branch URL, PR URL, grade.sh output, diffstat.
"""